# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore
# Service: auth-service
#
# PURPOSE:
#   Tells Docker which files to EXCLUDE when building the image.
#   Works exactly like .gitignore but for Docker's COPY instruction.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   Without this, `COPY . .` would copy node_modules into the image context,
#   which is slow (hundreds of MB) and wrong (the image installs its own
#   node_modules via npm install in the Dockerfile).
# =============================================================================

node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# Don't copy .env into the image — environment variables are injected
# at runtime by Docker Compose from the root .env file
.env

# Development files not needed in the container
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
*.md
